package generator

// Static CLAUDE.md block content for blocks that carry no graph dependency:
// MEDIATION-LOOP, CONCEPT-MAP, AGENT-MAP (no agents exist yet) are pure
// functions of the framework's own source tree, not of the domain graph --
// baking them here avoids re-implementing docstring scanning + live --help
// capture over the framework's Go source tree.
// OPERATOR-RECURSION is a template with one interpolation point (the active
// domain name). EMBEDDED-TOOLS and EMBEDDED-THINKING are NOT here — see
// RenderEmbeddedToolsBlock / RenderEmbeddedThinkingBlock in claudemd.go,
// which project them from internal/methodology's Tool / Section registries
// instead of hand-maintained text (the hand-maintained versions drifted
// stale: P1-6/TaskList #19 for tools, P1-1/Wave 4 for thinking).
//
// Each constant is the block's inner content -- the sentinel comment line
// plus body -- WITHOUT the BEGIN/END sentinel wrapper (WrapBlock adds that).
//
// Tool references below name the current Go CLI (`hotam <cmd>` /
// `go run ./cmd/hotam <cmd>`: gen-spec, what-now, apply-proposal, gate,
// all-violations). Steps with no Go command yet are marked as such rather
// than pointing at a command that does not exist in this build.

const mediationLoopText = "<!-- (generated by `hotam gen-spec` — do not hand-edit) -->\n\n### Mediation loop (how ANY input is processed)\n\nEvery input — idea, request, bug, hypothesis — six steps.\nRead-only input (a question, an explanation, a status check) needs only ORIENT +\na direct anchor-cited answer — steps 2-6 are for graph/code changes\n(R-agent-conduct-is-rules-not-tests: legalize actual practice, not aspirational rigor).\n\n1. **ORIENT** — reload pulse: top action · debt · context (LIVE-STATE below).\n   Full list: `hotam what-now` (R-boot-reload-three-facts, R-agent-never-lost).\n   New to the domain? Read top-down: purpose (Domain Map below / the domain\n   manifest) → `spec/docs/gen/PIPELINE.md` (the whole, stage by stage — the\n   SECOND document after the Domain Map, R-domain-overview-projection) →\n   Constitution index below → details (`spec/docs/gen/REQUIREMENTS.md`,\n   `spec/docs/gen/TENSIONS.md`, …).\n2. **LOCATE** — find what input touches: Constitution index below for R-anchors,\n   `spec/docs/gen/TENSIONS.md` for conflict clusters, `spec/docs/gen/REQUIREMENTS.md` for\n   full claims + assumptions.\n3. **CONFRONT** — check input vs reality: which SETTLED claims contradicted?\n   which Assumptions rested on / killed? already rejected — scan\n   RECENTLY-REJECTED below, cite replacement, don't re-derive (anti-relitigation).\n   Tool: `hotam confront <candidate-text>` ranks the candidate's lexical overlap\n   against SETTLED claims (duplicate guard) and REJECTED history (anti-relitigation).\n4. **TRANSLATE** — outcome → typed nodes: ProposedRequirement /\n   ProposedConflictTransition / ProposedRejection / ProposedConflict /\n   ProposedOperatorBudget / ProposedEntityType JSON, drafted as a `.json` file.\n   Tension found → Conflict node with axis + context + steward, never a silent\n   edit (R-no-hand-edit-graph, R-conflict-is-connector-node).\n   Meta-language: the business author writes the source claim in plain\n   natural language, in ANY language — they never write or see reserved\n   tokens. When that source asserts a hard universal/prohibition modality\n   (always/never/must/must-not/only-any, in whatever language the business\n   used), the AGENT — not the author — embeds the matching literal ALL-CAPS\n   English reserved token (ALWAYS, NEVER, MUST, MUST NOT, ONLY, ANY) into the\n   ProposedRequirement claim text it drafts here, e.g. \"экспорт всегда\n   должен шифроваться\" becomes \"Экспорт ALWAYS должен шифроваться\". This is\n   the same established pattern as RFC 2119's MUST/SHALL/SHOULD/MAY reserved\n   keywords in prose, except the embedding is an agent responsibility during\n   TRANSLATE, not an authoring convention imposed on humans — it makes the\n   opposite-marker conflict gate (`hotam confront`, the land-time semantic\n   gate) detect the assertion regardless of source language.\n5. **PRESENT** — show steward the proposal + anchors: resolves what, contradicts\n   what, replaces what. Steward decides (R-ai-presents-not-decides).\n6. **LAND** — after approval:\n   `hotam apply-proposal <file.json> --domain <path> --today YYYY-MM-DD`\n   → regen (`hotam gen-spec`) → gate: `hotam gate <target-anchor>` selects a\n   targeted test subset; `go test ./...` (the full suite) is MANDATORY at\n   wave/commit boundaries — closure verifies triggering diagnosis gone via\n   `hotam what-now` / `hotam all-violations` (R-verify-closure-per-action).\n\nHotam-Spec is an authored-executable-specification discipline, not a\ncode generator: an agent who understands the domain writes the model, its\nbehavior, and its tests BY HAND, general-before-specific; the engine holds\nthe structural floor (real symbols, real tests, real links) and generates\nonly derived projections (REQUIREMENTS/MODELS/TRACEABILITY/COVERAGE.md), never\nthe authored code itself (R-authored-spec-projections-are-derived).\n\nFounding a NEW domain follows this same general-to-specific canvas, 8 steps\n(R-domain-founded-in-wave-order):\n\n1. **Purpose, stakeholders, terminology** — manifest purpose/goals + Stakeholders + Axes.\n2. **Process and its scenarios** — a Process node naming stages, roles, and drives_entities.\n3. **Object model, by hand** (`spec/model/`) — the domain's aggregates/value-objects and\n   their fields, ALL models before any one model's detail (skeleton-first within the layer).\n4. **Operations, policies, invariants, by hand** (`spec/application/`, `spec/policy/`) — the\n   behavior the models above support: methods, gates, guards.\n5. **Executable tests, by hand** (`spec/tests/`, or beside the code they exercise) — proving\n   the operations and invariants above actually hold.\n6. **Requirements, linked to that code and those tests** — each Requirement records\n   `implemented_by` (file:symbol, WHERE it is embodied) and `verified_by` (file:test, WHERE\n   it is proven); ENFORCED requires both, real and resolvable (R-spec-link-embodied-vs-proven,\n   R-enforced-requires-enforcer-or-authored-link). SETTLED without a code link is honest\n   roadmap debt, never silently claimed ENFORCED.\n7. **Assumptions and conflicts** — the tensions and context this domain rests on.\n8. **Generated documentation and coverage audit** — `hotam gen-spec` renders\n   `spec/docs/gen/PIPELINE.md`/REQUIREMENTS.md/MODELS.md/TRACEABILITY.md/COVERAGE.md from the\n   authored layers above; diff against the domain's source prose right after step 1 — never\n   only at the end.\n\nEach step closes with `hotam gen-spec` + a check of `spec/docs/gen/PIPELINE.md`\nbefore the next step opens. The structural floor the engine mechanically checks\n(R-authored-spec-links-mechanically-checked) — implemented_by/verified_by resolve to real\nauthored code, tests are not vacuous (no bare `t.Log`/`t.Skip` standing in for proof), no\nlink orphaned by a later edit — is distinct from the MIRROR audit (a human or LLM reading\nrequirement-claim against authored code+test to certify it actually proves THAT claim,\nnot just that a link resolves; R-structural-floor-vs-mirror-audit): the engine guarantees\nthe link is real, the mirror audit certifies it is right.\n\nWriting nothing = valid outcome (\"contradicts R-x; rejected as R-y — cite R-z\")."

